      <descript>
         <abstract>Data are contained in a Microsoft Excel spreadsheets that describe abiotic and biotic study site characteristics in water bodies of the Bighorn Crags, Salmon River Mountains, from 1994-2011.</abstract>
         <purpose>This data set was developed to monitor amphibians on U. S. Forest Service lands.  Specifically, it examines the importance of landscape connectivity for amphibian conservation.</purpose>
         <supplinf>USGS-FRESC Study ID: 591</supplinf>
      </descript>
